@* The STATIC consumer of CascadeIsFixed.razor's cascade: its own [Parameter] Tag never changes, so
   under a FIXED cascade Blazor never re-parameterises it and it stays at 1 forever. Compiles
   perfectly well on its own -- it is the PARENT that is refused, which is the point (same shape as
   Gate/Plain.razor). *@
<span id="a">@Level</span>

@code {
    [Parameter] public string Tag { get; set; } = "";
    [CascadingParameter] public int Level { get; set; }
}
